DIGEST
SB 431 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Foil
Present law provides for "normal business hours" of any towing or storage company to be
from 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday, exclusive of legal holidays.
Proposed law retains present law and provides towing or storage companies that conduct
nonconsensual towing operations from private property make themselves available for the
release of personal property or the vehicle within ninety minutes of request outside normal
business hours and exclusive of legal holidays. Proposed law further provides towing or
storage companies conducting nonconsensual towing operations from private property that
are unavailable within ninety minutes of request to retrieve the vehicle or personal property
cannot charge the requester a storage fee the day of the facility closure or unavailability,
exclusive of legal holidays, suspending future storage fees until the next day of normal
business hours.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 32:1734(F); adds R.S. 32:1734(G) and (H))
